# AGENT CORE PRINCIPLES

> When code conflicts with rules, **rules prevail**. Full doc: `rules/AGENT-CORE-PRINCIPLES.md`

## Absolute rules (summary)

1. Layers: Interfaces → Application → Domain ← Infrastructure. Inner NEVER depends on outer.
2. Domain core: rich entities, aggregates, immutable VOs. NO frameworks in Domain.
3. Named BRs: GIVEN/WHEN/THEN, tested first, never duplicated.
4. State machines in Domain; invalid transitions throw.
5. Immutable past-tense domain events from aggregates.
6. Immutable history; corrections via new records.
7. Domain-generated IDs; mask sensitive data in logs/responses.
8. RBAC + ABAC in Application; tenant isolation every request.
9. Document use cases before code.
10. Versioned APIs (`/v1/`), structured errors, domain resource names.
11. Security from day one: MFA, rate limits, TLS, LGPD/GDPR.
12. TDD pyramid: 75% unit / 20% integration / 5% E2E. Domain ≥ 90% coverage.
13. AI in Application only: read-only, human confirm to persist, log all LLM calls.
14. Ubiquitous language: match glossary exactly.

